  "notes": "Erzya (эрзянь кель), Mordvinic (Uralic) language of Mordovia. Written in the Russian Cyrillic alphabet. Five vowels /a e i o u/ and a palatalised consonant series (/nʲ tʲ dʲ sʲ zʲ lʲ rʲ t͡sʲ/) marked, as in Russian, by ⟨ь⟩ or by a following front vowel — the palatalisation modifier is emitted as /ʲ/ rather than folded into the preceding consonant. ⟨ф х щ⟩ occur essentially only in Russian loanwords; the hard sign ⟨ъ⟩ is not used and is not mapped. Vowel harmony governs suffixes but is not a grapheme-level phenomenon.",
